The Republic of Portugal is issuing a 700mln French franc variable-rate bond due July 1995 at 100.05pct, lead manager Credit Commercial de France said.    The issue of unsecured, unsubordinated debt will have acoupon based on three-month LIBOR plus 20 basis points. If onany interest date this is 25 pct or more above three-monthParis Interbank Offered Rates then the interest rate will bethree-month PIBOR plus 30 basis points. Payment date is July24. There is a call at par at the end of the first year andthereafter on any interest payment date. Listing is Paris anddenominations are of 10,000 and 100,000 francs.    Fees total 50 basis points, with 25 points for selling and25 for management and underwriting combined including a sixbasis points praecipuum.    The issue is rated A by Moody's. REUTER&#3;